-- CDW to be bought by Madison Dearborn for $7.3 bln
-- 
-- Tue May 29, 2007 7:13pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/29/us-cdw-idUSWEN844620070529

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - CDW Corp. CDWC.O, a U.S. provider of technology products and services, said on Tuesday it agreed to be bought by Madison Dearborn Partners LLC for about $7.3 billion. 

 Under terms of the deal, CDW shareholders will get $87.75 in cash for each common CDW share, representing a premium of about 16.1 percent over CDW's closing share price of $75.56 on May 25, 2007, the last trading day prior to published reports regarding a potential transaction.